<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1437,620,1223]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName box="[267,504,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flammeaepennella">
<emphasis box="[267,504,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. flammeaepennella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, O. G." box="[512,647,873,899]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" refId="ref115328" refString="Costa, O. G. (1836) Fauna del Regno di Napoli ossia enumerazioni di tutti gli animali che abitano le diverse regioni di questo regno le acque che le bagnano contetente la descrizione de nuovi o poco esattemente conosciuti con figure ricavate da originali viventi e dipinte al naturale. Lepidotteri. Azzolino, Napoli, xi + [434] pp., 41 pls." type="book" year="1836">
<collectingRegion box="[512,579,873,899]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Costa</collectingRegion>
, 1836
</bibRefCitation>
was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stephens, 1834)" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1834" baseAuthorityName="Stephens" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[923,1274,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subocellea">
<emphasis box="[923,1075,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. subocellea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stephens, J. F." box="[1091,1265,873,899]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="33 - 40" refId="ref132647" refString="Stephens, J. F. (1834 - 35) Illustrations of British Entomology; or, a Synopsis of Indigenous Insects, containing their generic and species distinctions; with an account of their metamorphoses, times of appearance, localities, food and economy, as far as practicable. Haustellata 4. Baldwin &amp; Cradock, London, 436 pp., pls. 33 - 40." type="book chapter" year="1834">Stephens, 1834</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tremewan, W. G." pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="213 - 232" refId="ref134853" refString="Tremewan, W. G. (1977) The publications on Lepidoptera by O. G. and A. Costa and the nominal taxa described therein. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Historical Series, 5.3., 213 - 232." type="book chapter" year="1977">Tremewan (1977: 222)</bibRefCitation>
. This synonymy has been followed since, even though the otherwise recognized geographic distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stephens" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[337,491,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subocellea">
<emphasis box="[337,491,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. subocellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not extend to the Napoli area, the 
<typeStatus box="[955,1003,945,971]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<emphasis box="[1138,1384,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName box="[1138,1380,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flammeaepennella">E. flammeaepennella</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The painting of 
<taxonomicName box="[326,561,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flammeaepennella">
<emphasis box="[326,561,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. flammeaepennella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
O.G. 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, O. G." box="[627,760,981,1007]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" refId="ref115328" refString="Costa, O. G. (1836) Fauna del Regno di Napoli ossia enumerazioni di tutti gli animali che abitano le diverse regioni di questo regno le acque che le bagnano contetente la descrizione de nuovi o poco esattemente conosciuti con figure ricavate da originali viventi e dipinte al naturale. Lepidotteri. Azzolino, Napoli, xi + [434] pp., 41 pls." type="book" year="1836">
<collectingRegion box="[627,694,981,1007]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Costa</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity box="[704,760,981,1007]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.66344" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="in" value="1836.0">1836</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
in the original description (Plate V, fig. 8A) displays brighter forewing pattern and darker hindwings than observed in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stephens" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[824,974,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subocellea">
<emphasis box="[824,974,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. subocellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of genitalia of recent specimens from Napoli display significant differences in both male and female genitalia between 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stephens" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[1238,1389,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subocellea">
<emphasis box="[1238,1389,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. subocellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the specimens from Napoli. The verbal description: “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Alis anticis flaviis, fasciis duabus albis, punctis minutissimis atris adspersis; fimbria longa 
<taxonomicName box="[607,690,1126,1151]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cinerea">cinerea</taxonomicName>
nigro-punctulata: alis posticis plumbeis”
</emphasis>
, also points out towards a brighter-colored species than 
<emphasis box="[551,710,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stephens" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[551,706,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subocellea">E. subocellea</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Based on this evidence, 
<taxonomicName box="[989,1226,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flammeaepennella">
<emphasis box="[989,1226,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. flammeaepennella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here considered a valid species., 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[383,485,1197,1223]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">stat. rev.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
